### ============================================================
### INSTRUMENT: Rahim Organizational Conflict Inventory-II (ROCI-II)
### Developer: M. Afzalur Rahim (1983)
### Format: 28 Likert-scale items (1–5) | Normative (interval) scoring
### Subscales: integrating, obliging, dominating, avoiding, compromising
### Level: Individual
### Admin time: 10–15 minutes
### ============================================================
###
### ⚠ NEW SCHEMA REQUIREMENTS FOR THIS INSTRUMENT:
###
###   "scale_range": { "min": 1, "max": 5, "labels": { ... } }
###     Defines the Likert anchor labels. Unlike the existing "scale" type
###     (which may default to 1–10 or similar), this instrument uses a
###     strict 1–5 range with named anchors.
###
###   "subscale": "integrating" | "obliging" | "dominating" | "avoiding" | "compromising"
###     Each item belongs to exactly one subscale. The scoring engine
###     averages items within each subscale to produce a subscale score.
###
###   "scoring": { "method": "normative" }
###     Unlike TKI's ipsative method, ROCI-II uses interval scoring.
###     Subscale scores can be compared across individuals and groups.
###     Enables parametric statistics (t-tests, ANOVA, regression).
###
###   "reverse_scored": true
###     Items flagged with this field must have their raw response
###     subtracted from (max + 1) before subscale averaging.
###     e.g., for a 1–5 scale: reverse = 6 - raw_score.
###     ROCI-II dominating items 13, 14 are reverse scored.
###
###   "relationship_target": "supervisor" | "subordinate" | "peer"
###     ROCI-II has three parallel forms — one for each relationship type.
###     The same item text applies but norms differ by target. This field
###     routes the response to the correct norm table at scoring time.
###
### ============================================================

POST http://localhost:3030/api/surveys/templates
Content-Type: application/json
